# Vault (knowledge paths)

Consult `vault_storage.md` in this framework for the full lifecycle table and templates.

## When this applies

When editing topics or integrating new knowledge into the vault, follow `vault_storage.md` and use `topic-manage` for lifecycle checks (split) after substantive topic changes.

## Topic file sections (active topics in `topics/`)

Use the structure in `vault_storage.md` (Current State, Decisions, Open Questions, Action Items, Key People, References).

## Reference knowledge (`knowledge/*.md`)

Stable reference articles—no required template or durable-topic lifecycle sections. Freeform.

## Records (`records/*.md`)

One file per user message that **changed** stored vault knowledge. Template in `vault_storage.md`. Do not create records for read-only queries.
